ğŸ”“ ğŸ– ğŸ½ index ğŸš‚ â¡ï¸ ğŸ¬ğŸš‚

Returns an integer representing the value of the byte at the given index index. A negative index is assumed to be relative to the end of the data.

This method treats the byte at the index as if it was an unsigned value, that is the front most bit is also counted towards the value and does not indicate the sign. The value is therefore always positive.

Nothingness is returned if the index is out of range.
